WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:08.775 align:middle line:90%
[ Silence ]

00:00:11.411 --> 00:00:14.114 align:middle line:84%
>> I think many people
today don't know what

00:00:14.114 --> 00:00:15.248 align:middle line:90%
to believe anymore.

00:00:15.248 --> 00:00:17.484 align:middle line:84%
>> People are basically
going to keep on look

00:00:17.484 --> 00:00:19.686 align:middle line:84%
to [inaudible] tell them
what really happened.

00:00:19.686 --> 00:00:22.022 align:middle line:84%
>> I felt like something
was watching me.

00:00:22.022 --> 00:00:23.990 align:middle line:84%
>> We weren't given
all the information.

00:00:23.990 --> 00:00:27.694 align:middle line:84%
You weren't told
the entire story.

00:00:27.694 --> 00:00:34.434 align:middle line:84%
>> And now, the host of the
nationally syndicated coast

00:00:34.434 --> 00:00:38.305 align:middle line:84%
to coast AM and GaiamTV
bring you Beyond Belief

00:00:38.305 --> 00:00:41.041 align:middle line:90%
with George Noory.

00:00:41.041 --> 00:00:42.843 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Well,
welcome to Beyond Belief.

00:00:42.843 --> 00:00:45.979 align:middle line:84%
You know I have always believed
that if you can't take care

00:00:45.979 --> 00:00:49.116 align:middle line:84%
of your health, you can't take
other people you care about,

00:00:49.116 --> 00:00:50.383 align:middle line:90%
your loved ones.

00:00:50.383 --> 00:00:53.487 align:middle line:84%
And so your health is by
far the most critical thing

00:00:53.487 --> 00:00:55.522 align:middle line:90%
that you can take care of.

00:00:55.522 --> 00:00:58.992 align:middle line:84%
Our guest tonight on Beyond
Belief is the noted researcher

00:00:58.992 --> 00:01:02.929 align:middle line:84%
and author, who is going to be
probably save many lives just

00:01:02.929 --> 00:01:04.164 align:middle line:90%
on this program alone.

00:01:04.164 --> 00:01:06.333 align:middle line:90%
Please welcome Christian Wilde.

00:01:06.333 --> 00:01:11.204 align:middle line:84%
[Applause] How are
are you my friend?

00:01:11.204 --> 00:01:12.105 align:middle line:90%
Good to see you.

00:01:12.105 --> 00:01:13.406 align:middle line:90%
Have a seat.

00:01:13.406 --> 00:01:14.441 align:middle line:90%
Always a pleasure.

00:01:14.441 --> 00:01:15.809 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
Always a pleasure.

00:01:15.809 --> 00:01:18.078 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Do you know
how many people you have saved

00:01:18.078 --> 00:01:19.980 align:middle line:90%
over the years?

00:01:19.980 --> 00:01:21.714 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
We have saved.

00:01:21.714 --> 00:01:24.951 align:middle line:84%
If you didn't give me that
forum George, they would never

00:01:24.951 --> 00:01:27.921 align:middle line:84%
of heard about the things
that we were talking about.

00:01:27.921 --> 00:01:29.723 align:middle line:90%
And therefore, benefit from it.

00:01:29.723 --> 00:01:34.294 align:middle line:84%
I have no way of knowing except
probably for sure eight people

00:01:34.294 --> 00:01:37.264 align:middle line:84%
that we know, because
they've come back on the show

00:01:37.264 --> 00:01:40.734 align:middle line:84%
after having been in
late stage heart failure.

00:01:40.734 --> 00:01:43.970 align:middle line:84%
And we were able to
get them into trials.

00:01:43.970 --> 00:01:47.474 align:middle line:84%
As their advocates, they've
gotten their stem cells.

00:01:47.474 --> 00:01:50.410 align:middle line:84%
Takes about 45 minutes
as you know.

00:01:50.410 --> 00:01:53.547 align:middle line:84%
And the patient goes
home the next day.

00:01:53.547 --> 00:01:57.851 align:middle line:84%
Six weeks later a person who
couldn't negotiate a trip

00:01:57.851 --> 00:02:00.020 align:middle line:84%
to the broom without
being exhausted.

00:02:00.020 --> 00:02:00.854 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: Yes.

00:02:00.854 --> 00:02:02.055 align:middle line:90%
Couldn't even walk three steps.

00:02:02.055 --> 00:02:03.256 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: They
told you that in the show.

00:02:03.256 --> 00:02:05.559 align:middle line:84%
All of a sudden they're
walking 2, 3 miles a day.

00:02:05.559 --> 00:02:08.261 align:middle line:90%
It is absolutely phenomenal.

00:02:08.261 --> 00:02:09.529 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory:
I'm just wondering

00:02:09.529 --> 00:02:11.665 align:middle line:84%
if we should all get injections
with stem cells one day.

00:02:11.665 --> 00:02:13.266 align:middle line:84%
But we'll talk about
some of that.

00:02:13.266 --> 00:02:14.634 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
Actually, we may.

00:02:14.634 --> 00:02:16.302 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: You know, I
was just telling the audience

00:02:16.302 --> 00:02:20.874 align:middle line:84%
as I introduced you, how
important it is for everybody,

00:02:20.874 --> 00:02:23.643 align:middle line:84%
each individual to take
care of themselves.

00:02:23.643 --> 00:02:24.677 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: Absolutely.

00:02:24.677 --> 00:02:27.113 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: I
mean, you lose that.

00:02:27.113 --> 00:02:28.515 align:middle line:90%
What good is money?

00:02:28.515 --> 00:02:29.883 align:middle line:90%
What good is anything?

00:02:29.883 --> 00:02:33.453 align:middle line:84%
What good is the ability to
help your family if you're gone?

00:02:33.453 --> 00:02:34.521 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: That's true.

00:02:34.521 --> 00:02:36.623 align:middle line:84%
If you're not around
and the old saying,

00:02:36.623 --> 00:02:38.358 align:middle line:84%
"If you got your health,
you got everything."

00:02:38.358 --> 00:02:39.559 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: Absolutely.

00:02:39.559 --> 00:02:41.394 align:middle line:84%
How did you get interested
in all this Christian?

00:02:41.394 --> 00:02:44.464 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: Well, I
was in a different business.

00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:46.733 align:middle line:84%
You know I was in the music
industry for 20 so years.

00:02:46.733 --> 00:02:49.069 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: I may have
you sing a song acapella.

00:02:49.069 --> 00:02:50.737 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: I
don't know about that.

00:02:50.737 --> 00:02:51.538 align:middle line:90%
But

00:02:51.538 --> 00:02:52.939 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: We'll vote.

00:02:52.939 --> 00:02:54.975 align:middle line:84%
We'll vote a little bit later on
to see if they want to see you

00:02:54.975 --> 00:02:56.876 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: But
that's been a long time

00:02:56.876 --> 00:02:58.511 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: I love
putting people on the spot.

00:02:58.511 --> 00:02:59.879 align:middle line:90%
How are you?

00:02:59.879 --> 00:03:02.549 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: But at
one point I became concerned

00:03:02.549 --> 00:03:06.086 align:middle line:84%
about friends of mine that
were dying of heart disease.

00:03:06.086 --> 00:03:09.956 align:middle line:84%
I would talk to their families
and the wife might say,

00:03:09.956 --> 00:03:12.726 align:middle line:84%
"Christian, my husband had
a complete physical the

00:03:12.726 --> 00:03:14.527 align:middle line:90%
week before.

00:03:14.527 --> 00:03:16.396 align:middle line:90%
A nuclear treadmill.

00:03:16.396 --> 00:03:18.531 align:middle line:90%
Cholesterol was perfect.

00:03:18.531 --> 00:03:21.601 align:middle line:84%
Doctor said that I don't need
to see you for another year.

00:03:21.601 --> 00:03:24.537 align:middle line:84%
And three days he
died in his sleep.

00:03:24.537 --> 00:03:27.707 align:middle line:84%
And I would hear it
time and time again.

00:03:27.707 --> 00:03:30.010 align:middle line:84%
And I became concerned
with what is there

00:03:30.010 --> 00:03:32.712 align:middle line:90%
out there that's hidden?

00:03:32.712 --> 00:03:37.250 align:middle line:84%
What hidden heart attack
risk are going undetected

00:03:37.250 --> 00:03:39.486 align:middle line:90%
by physicians?

00:03:39.486 --> 00:03:43.623 align:middle line:84%
So, it took five and a half
years to write the book.

00:03:43.623 --> 00:03:45.191 align:middle line:90%
The first book.

00:03:45.191 --> 00:03:48.361 align:middle line:84%
During that time I had
mortgage on my house.

00:03:48.361 --> 00:03:50.697 align:middle line:90%
And just dedicate myself

00:03:50.697 --> 00:03:56.870 align:middle line:84%
to finding not only the hidden
risk factors but what you can do

00:03:56.870 --> 00:04:00.740 align:middle line:84%
to be involved in your own
health care so you could see

00:04:00.740 --> 00:04:02.442 align:middle line:84%
to it that when you
talk to your physician,

00:04:02.442 --> 00:04:05.245 align:middle line:84%
you could present your
case intelligently.

00:04:05.245 --> 00:04:07.047 align:middle line:90%
And so that's where we started.

00:04:07.047 --> 00:04:09.182 align:middle line:90%
And it's been very good.

00:04:09.182 --> 00:04:11.651 align:middle line:84%
Mr. Noory here has
been kind to me.

00:04:11.651 --> 00:04:14.921 align:middle line:84%
He's had me on that show
so many, many times.

00:04:14.921 --> 00:04:16.089 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Can I
tell them how many times?

00:04:16.089 --> 00:04:17.190 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: Sure.

00:04:17.190 --> 00:04:20.093 align:middle line:84%
We figured out it
was over 300 times.

00:04:20.093 --> 00:04:22.128 align:middle line:90%
Two times a month average.

00:04:22.128 --> 00:04:23.296 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory:
Little news clip.

00:04:23.296 --> 00:04:24.798 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
Little news shows.

00:04:24.798 --> 00:04:26.199 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:04:26.199 --> 00:04:28.468 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: But I'm telling
you, and we'll get into this.

00:04:28.468 --> 00:04:30.570 align:middle line:84%
Some of the people that
have called the program,

00:04:30.570 --> 00:04:33.073 align:middle line:84%
these were regular coast
to coast listeners.

00:04:33.073 --> 00:04:38.244 align:middle line:84%
People who were at deaths door
and I mean, one individual said,

00:04:38.244 --> 00:04:41.448 align:middle line:84%
as I mentioned, he could
barely walk three steps.

00:04:41.448 --> 00:04:45.385 align:middle line:84%
Christian got him into an
experimental stem cell program.

00:04:45.385 --> 00:04:46.619 align:middle line:90%
The guy's jogging.

00:04:46.619 --> 00:04:47.187 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: Yes.

00:04:47.187 --> 00:04:48.154 align:middle line:90%
He's jogging.

00:04:48.154 --> 00:04:50.924 align:middle line:84%
That was after seven
heart attacks.

00:04:50.924 --> 00:04:55.428 align:middle line:84%
By the time he called George,
he had five heart attacks.

00:04:55.428 --> 00:04:58.298 align:middle line:84%
And it took me two years
to get him into a trial.

00:04:58.298 --> 00:05:01.601 align:middle line:84%
But I promised him on the
air, I would stay with you

00:05:01.601 --> 00:05:03.970 align:middle line:84%
as your advocate
to get this done.

00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:07.807 align:middle line:84%
Well, by the time we got him
in, he had his 7th heart attack.

00:05:07.807 --> 00:05:09.075 align:middle line:90%
But isn't that amazing?

00:05:09.075 --> 00:05:11.111 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Well,
that's the other thing.

00:05:11.111 --> 00:05:14.714 align:middle line:84%
You know, when someone calls
and says, "I need help."

00:05:14.714 --> 00:05:17.050 align:middle line:84%
We really don't know how
much time they have left.

00:05:17.050 --> 00:05:18.385 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: No we don't.

00:05:18.385 --> 00:05:20.286 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: And so, you
move at a rapid clip to try

00:05:20.286 --> 00:05:21.654 align:middle line:90%
to get them into the program.

00:05:21.654 --> 00:05:23.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: There was
one fellow recently, George.

00:05:23.890 --> 00:05:26.159 align:middle line:84%
A friend of his called
me and said,

00:05:26.159 --> 00:05:27.694 align:middle line:90%
"Would you try to help him?"

00:05:27.694 --> 00:05:30.964 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the most
gracious man you'll ever meet.

00:05:30.964 --> 00:05:33.400 align:middle line:90%
And so I said, "Okay, I'll him.

00:05:33.400 --> 00:05:35.268 align:middle line:84%
Tell him I'm going to
call him so he'll know."

00:05:35.268 --> 00:05:37.070 align:middle line:90%
And so I called him and he said,

00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:38.972 align:middle line:84%
"Oh don't worry about
me, Chris."

00:05:38.972 --> 00:05:41.674 align:middle line:84%
He said, "I'm ready to meet my
[inaudible] my doctor's been

00:05:41.674 --> 00:05:44.544 align:middle line:84%
telling me for two years
to prepare to die."

00:05:44.544 --> 00:05:46.246 align:middle line:90%
He says, "Don't worry about me."

00:05:46.246 --> 00:05:47.647 align:middle line:84%
I said, "Well, I am
worried about you.

00:05:47.647 --> 00:05:49.549 align:middle line:90%
Let me ask you some questions."

00:05:49.549 --> 00:05:53.052 align:middle line:84%
Because I need to pre qualify
these people medically.

00:05:53.052 --> 00:05:55.355 align:middle line:90%
And he gave me the answers.

00:05:55.355 --> 00:05:58.925 align:middle line:84%
And I e mailed the director of
one of the major Universities.

00:05:58.925 --> 00:06:01.594 align:middle line:84%
I said, "Can we help
this fellow?"

00:06:01.594 --> 00:06:05.598 align:middle line:84%
He writes me back, "Call
Pamela in the morning.

00:06:05.598 --> 00:06:07.434 align:middle line:90%
Schedule him to come in.

00:06:07.434 --> 00:06:09.202 align:middle line:90%
We're going to save this man."

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:13.239 align:middle line:84%
And he went in since then and
had his own stem cells taken

00:06:13.239 --> 00:06:16.309 align:middle line:84%
from his leg and
injected into his heart.

00:06:16.309 --> 00:06:17.277 align:middle line:90%
We'll talk about that

00:06:17.277 --> 00:06:17.844 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: Yes.

00:06:17.844 --> 00:06:18.945 align:middle line:90%
Just amazing.

00:06:18.945 --> 00:06:21.614 align:middle line:90%
You deserve a round of applause.

00:06:21.614 --> 00:06:24.184 align:middle line:90%
[Applause].

00:06:24.184 --> 00:06:26.152 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: George
cares about his listeners.

00:06:26.152 --> 00:06:27.987 align:middle line:90%
There's no question about that.

00:06:27.987 --> 00:06:29.956 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: When people
come down with diseases,

00:06:29.956 --> 00:06:33.893 align:middle line:84%
sometimes you know, it takes
a long time to affect them.

00:06:33.893 --> 00:06:35.962 align:middle line:84%
Heart attacks are
sometimes [inaudible].

00:06:35.962 --> 00:06:37.664 align:middle line:90%
I mean, I've got to you.

00:06:37.664 --> 00:06:39.833 align:middle line:84%
You know, when I'm
preparing for coast to coast

00:06:39.833 --> 00:06:43.436 align:middle line:84%
and you read a story that this
person is a prominent actor

00:06:43.436 --> 00:06:45.872 align:middle line:84%
or somebody just keeled
over, died of a heart attack.

00:06:45.872 --> 00:06:48.541 align:middle line:90%
Showing no symptoms at all.

00:06:48.541 --> 00:06:49.742 align:middle line:90%
That's darn scary.

00:06:49.742 --> 00:06:51.878 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: That's
scary because we wonder.

00:06:51.878 --> 00:06:53.246 align:middle line:84%
And we've talked about
[inaudible] where I sit

00:06:53.246 --> 00:06:56.115 align:middle line:84%
in some shows and people like
that you've called me about.

00:06:56.115 --> 00:06:59.486 align:middle line:84%
We wonder if these people
whether the finest medical

00:06:59.486 --> 00:07:02.222 align:middle line:84%
attention they have how
does this happen to them?

00:07:02.222 --> 00:07:06.960 align:middle line:84%
And if it happens to them, what
assurance is there for you and I

00:07:06.960 --> 00:07:09.128 align:middle line:84%
that it's not going
to happen to us?

00:07:09.128 --> 00:07:11.898 align:middle line:84%
You must become involved
in your own health care.

00:07:11.898 --> 00:07:14.734 align:middle line:84%
Because nobody will
have invested interest

00:07:14.734 --> 00:07:16.769 align:middle line:90%
in it more than you.

00:07:16.769 --> 00:07:19.639 align:middle line:84%
But to answer George's
question, that's true.

00:07:19.639 --> 00:07:21.708 align:middle line:84%
People who have cancer
or Parkinson's,

00:07:21.708 --> 00:07:25.011 align:middle line:84%
they get a diagnosis
of prostate cancer.

00:07:25.011 --> 00:07:27.280 align:middle line:84%
They're going to be around for
a long time before it takes

00:07:27.280 --> 00:07:28.515 align:middle line:90%
its toll.

00:07:28.515 --> 00:07:31.818 align:middle line:84%
That individual has time
to spend with his family,

00:07:31.818 --> 00:07:34.787 align:middle line:84%
to mend some fences
with some people.

00:07:34.787 --> 00:07:36.656 align:middle line:90%
To take some trips.

00:07:36.656 --> 00:07:38.791 align:middle line:90%
To look at his bucket list.

00:07:38.791 --> 00:07:41.528 align:middle line:84%
But as George said, with a
heart attack, it's sudden.

00:07:41.528 --> 00:07:44.998 align:middle line:84%
A man can be 47 years
old, raises his children.

00:07:44.998 --> 00:07:47.233 align:middle line:90%
Got three kids or a woman.

00:07:47.233 --> 00:07:50.270 align:middle line:84%
And all of a sudden, it's the
number one killer in the world.

00:07:50.270 --> 00:07:52.639 align:middle line:90%
And it strikes too often.

00:07:52.639 --> 00:07:54.674 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: In many cases,

00:07:54.674 --> 00:07:58.111 align:middle line:84%
had he done some
preventative medicine

00:07:58.111 --> 00:08:01.681 align:middle line:84%
or gotten certain tests,
would he have known

00:08:01.681 --> 00:08:03.583 align:middle line:90%
that he had a potential problem?

00:08:03.583 --> 00:08:05.351 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
He would George.

00:08:05.351 --> 00:08:10.356 align:middle line:84%
I recommend that everybody try
to get a nuclear treadmill.

00:08:10.356 --> 00:08:13.226 align:middle line:84%
Because I continually
hear people say,

00:08:13.226 --> 00:08:16.729 align:middle line:84%
"Before my heart
attack, I had been told

00:08:16.729 --> 00:08:20.233 align:middle line:84%
that I had no risk factors,
everything was perfect.

00:08:20.233 --> 00:08:22.936 align:middle line:90%
Nothing to be concerned about.

00:08:22.936 --> 00:08:26.940 align:middle line:84%
And then I had a heart attack
and they found out then

00:08:26.940 --> 00:08:29.943 align:middle line:84%
that I have three
major blocked arteries.

00:08:29.943 --> 00:08:32.445 align:middle line:90%
97 percent, 80 percent.

00:08:32.445 --> 00:08:33.979 align:middle line:90%
I had no symptoms."

00:08:33.979 --> 00:08:38.751 align:middle line:84%
The nuclear treadmill tells you
right now, you've got a problem.

00:08:38.751 --> 00:08:40.353 align:middle line:90%
We've got to correct it.

00:08:40.353 --> 00:08:41.753 align:middle line:90%
And we can go in to do a stem.

00:08:41.753 --> 00:08:43.423 align:middle line:84%
And this information
is as much good

00:08:43.423 --> 00:08:45.858 align:middle line:84%
for the women as
it is for the men.

00:08:45.858 --> 00:08:47.894 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: It's smart,
preventative business.

00:08:47.894 --> 00:08:50.330 align:middle line:84%
You know, I look at
the body like a car.

00:08:50.330 --> 00:08:51.798 align:middle line:90%
I'm the kind of guy.

00:08:51.798 --> 00:08:54.000 align:middle line:84%
I don't want to drive
a car and have it break

00:08:54.000 --> 00:08:56.369 align:middle line:84%
down on the freeway at 3
o'clock in the morning,

00:08:56.369 --> 00:08:58.071 align:middle line:90%
leaving coast to coast.

00:08:58.071 --> 00:08:59.339 align:middle line:90%
I want to make sure

00:08:59.339 --> 00:09:03.443 align:middle line:84%
that whatever maintenance
I do, it's done prior to.

00:09:03.443 --> 00:09:06.279 align:middle line:84%
It's tuned up, the
oil is changed

00:09:06.279 --> 00:09:08.147 align:middle line:90%
and everything is humming along.

00:09:08.147 --> 00:09:09.983 align:middle line:84%
I don't want that
