want to share with you

00:18:30.009 --> 00:18:33.412 align:middle line:90%
and our gracious host here toad.

00:18:33.412 --> 00:18:39.084 align:middle line:84%
And that is, when somebody
has an open heart surgery

00:18:39.084 --> 00:18:41.253 align:middle line:90%
and times goes by.

00:18:41.253 --> 00:18:46.025 align:middle line:84%
If the physician hasn't found
out your hidden factors,

00:18:46.025 --> 00:18:47.660 align:middle line:90%
you'll be under the scalpel,

00:18:47.660 --> 00:18:50.930 align:middle line:84%
unfortunately 10
or 15 years later.

00:18:50.930 --> 00:18:55.568 align:middle line:84%
A lot of these people can't
sustain that operation.

00:18:55.568 --> 00:18:58.637 align:middle line:84%
They captain go through
open heart surgery.

00:18:58.637 --> 00:19:03.075 align:middle line:84%
So what happens is the physician
says, "I can't allow you to die

00:19:03.075 --> 00:19:05.411 align:middle line:90%
on the table or a week later.

00:19:05.411 --> 00:19:08.080 align:middle line:84%
Your condition is
just too far gone.

00:19:08.080 --> 00:19:10.950 align:middle line:90%
You need a heart valve.

00:19:10.950 --> 00:19:13.686 align:middle line:84%
But weigh can't put
in a heart valve."

00:19:13.686 --> 00:19:16.255 align:middle line:84%
Now, normally a heart
valve would be a mitral

00:19:16.255 --> 00:19:20.125 align:middle line:84%
or an aortic valve that they
would get from a tissue valve.

00:19:20.125 --> 00:19:22.161 align:middle line:84%
They'd get it from
a cow a bovine.

00:19:22.161 --> 00:19:23.996 align:middle line:90%
Or they get it from a pig.

00:19:23.996 --> 00:19:25.965 align:middle line:90%
That's a poor sign.

00:19:25.965 --> 00:19:33.205 align:middle line:84%
But our friends at a company
called, Edward's Life Sciences,

00:19:33.205 --> 00:19:35.708 align:middle line:84%
decided to take on
that challenge.

00:19:35.708 --> 00:19:39.411 align:middle line:84%
What about these people who are
going to die that you could save

00:19:39.411 --> 00:19:42.882 align:middle line:84%
if there was a way you
could put a heart valve

00:19:42.882 --> 00:19:46.652 align:middle line:84%
in a mechanical one
without opening the chest

00:19:46.652 --> 00:19:51.190 align:middle line:84%
and presenting them
for open heart surgery.

00:19:51.190 --> 00:19:55.561 align:middle line:84%
The way they do it
is they put the valve

00:19:55.561 --> 00:19:56.729 align:middle line:90%
which I'm going to show you.

00:19:56.729 --> 00:20:01.433 align:middle line:84%
It's called a sapien
transcatheter heart valve.

00:20:01.433 --> 00:20:03.769 align:middle line:90%
They put it on a catheter head.

00:20:03.769 --> 00:20:06.205 align:middle line:90%
They go in their femoral artery.

00:20:06.205 --> 00:20:11.076 align:middle line:84%
Up into your aortic valve
and pop it in place.

00:20:11.076 --> 00:20:12.177 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory:
Pop it in place?

00:20:12.177 --> 00:20:13.445 align:middle line:90%
Just like there's no surgery?

00:20:13.445 --> 00:20:14.747 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: No surgery.

00:20:14.747 --> 00:20:15.881 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Let's see
what this thing looks like.

00:20:15.881 --> 00:20:16.749 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: I'm
going to show it to you.

00:20:16.749 --> 00:20:18.117 align:middle line:90%
But I want to tell it to you.

00:20:18.117 --> 00:20:19.385 align:middle line:90%
We got to be careful.

00:20:19.385 --> 00:20:21.053 align:middle line:90%
This is a real one.

00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:26.825 align:middle line:90%
This one cost $30,000.

00:20:26.825 --> 00:20:28.394 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: $30,000.

00:20:28.394 --> 00:20:31.597 align:middle line:84%
You obviously have to give
it back to the company.

00:20:31.597 --> 00:20:32.598 align:middle line:90%
What's it made out of?

00:20:32.598 --> 00:20:33.599 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian it's
made out of a kind

00:20:33.599 --> 00:20:35.768 align:middle line:90%
of a teflon type of material.

00:20:35.768 --> 00:20:37.269 align:middle line:90%
You can handle it.

00:20:37.269 --> 00:20:42.675 align:middle line:90%
That's the sapien heart valve.

00:20:42.675 --> 00:20:44.243 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory:
Little tiny thing.

00:20:44.243 --> 00:20:45.678 align:middle line:90%
You got a picture of that.

00:20:45.678 --> 00:20:47.046 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
It keeps you alive.

00:20:47.046 --> 00:20:50.716 align:middle line:90%
It's a gravity valve which means

00:20:50.716 --> 00:20:52.051 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: Pretty rigid.

00:20:52.051 --> 00:20:53.686 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: Pretty
rigid I haven't even felt it.

00:20:53.686 --> 00:20:56.722 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: It's rigid
and so they just pop it?

00:20:56.722 --> 00:20:58.123 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: Yes.

00:20:58.123 --> 00:21:02.494 align:middle line:84%
It goes right over your old
diseased valve that's calcified.

00:21:02.494 --> 00:21:05.631 align:middle line:84%
Then it goes in there, they
pop it with a balloon and poof.

00:21:05.631 --> 00:21:06.966 align:middle line:90%
It takes its place.

00:21:06.966 --> 00:21:08.701 align:middle line:90%
Yes. And then

00:21:08.701 --> 00:21:13.372 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Why
does that cost so much?

00:21:13.372 --> 00:21:15.941 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: Because
I guess that 7 or 10 years

00:21:15.941 --> 00:21:18.744 align:middle line:84%
