trials and millions

00:21:18.744 --> 00:21:20.412 align:middle line:90%
and millions of dollars.

00:21:20.412 --> 00:21:22.114 align:middle line:84%
It's unfortunate, but
that is what happens.

00:21:22.114 --> 00:21:23.248 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: I mean,

00:21:23.248 --> 00:21:25.517 align:middle line:84%
it's like a toilet part
you get for only $15.

00:21:25.517 --> 00:21:26.819 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: Yes.

00:21:26.819 --> 00:21:28.754 align:middle line:84%
It's like the mechanic says
to you, "I put a new valve

00:21:28.754 --> 00:21:31.490 align:middle line:90%
in your car or a new seal.

00:21:31.490 --> 00:21:34.159 align:middle line:90%
Seal costs $2.50.

00:21:34.159 --> 00:21:36.061 align:middle line:84%
Where it costs $800
to put it in."

00:21:36.061 --> 00:21:37.262 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: The labor.

00:21:37.262 --> 00:21:37.963 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: That's
a good example, right?

00:21:37.963 --> 00:21:38.497 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: Yes.

00:21:38.497 --> 00:21:39.898 align:middle line:90%
It sure is.

00:21:39.898 --> 00:21:40.733 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: So that's
one of the new breakthroughs.

00:21:40.733 --> 00:21:41.533 align:middle line:90%
Something to look forward to.

00:21:41.533 --> 00:21:42.868 align:middle line:90%
You might have relatives

00:21:42.868 --> 00:21:46.972 align:middle line:84%
that have insufficient
heart valve problems.

00:21:46.972 --> 00:21:48.173 align:middle line:90%
Mitral valve.

00:21:48.173 --> 00:21:50.275 align:middle line:84%
Mitral valve hasn't
been approved yet.

00:21:50.275 --> 00:21:53.545 align:middle line:84%
There are 50,000 of
these already in people.

00:21:53.545 --> 00:21:55.414 align:middle line:84%
The mitral is about
two years away.

00:21:55.414 --> 00:21:57.182 align:middle line:90%
It's a little bit more complex.

00:21:57.182 --> 00:21:58.584 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: The ancients.

00:21:58.584 --> 00:22:01.019 align:middle line:84%
They lived to about
30, 40 years old.

00:22:01.019 --> 00:22:04.056 align:middle line:84%
Or that was old age
in those days.

00:22:04.056 --> 00:22:06.325 align:middle line:84%
You know, now we're
into the late 70's.

00:22:06.325 --> 00:22:08.827 align:middle line:84%
And some people even
longer than that.

00:22:08.827 --> 00:22:10.929 align:middle line:90%
Is it because of technology?

00:22:10.929 --> 00:22:14.733 align:middle line:84%
What has changed the
lifestyle of people

00:22:14.733 --> 00:22:19.104 align:middle line:84%
where the ancients died in
their 40's and now we're dying

00:22:19.104 --> 00:22:20.906 align:middle line:90%
in our late 70's and 80's.

00:22:20.906 --> 00:22:21.707 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: 90's.

00:22:21.707 --> 00:22:23.575 align:middle line:90%
A lot of people.

00:22:23.575 --> 00:22:24.943 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory:
Is it technology?

00:22:24.943 --> 00:22:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: A lot of
it is technology and knowledge

00:22:28.180 --> 00:22:31.316 align:middle line:84%
that you pick up and say,
"I'm going to get involved

00:22:31.316 --> 00:22:32.618 align:middle line:90%
