00:23:14.927 --> 00:23:16.528 align:middle line:90%
to cut a little slack.

00:23:16.528 --> 00:23:18.831 align:middle line:84%
If you're going to be
dedicated your life

00:23:18.831 --> 00:23:21.200 align:middle line:84%
and your average
life span is 58.

00:23:21.200 --> 00:23:22.267 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory:
Surely remarkable.

00:23:22.267 --> 00:23:23.635 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: It is.

00:23:23.635 --> 00:23:25.771 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: When you talked
about atrial defibrillation,

00:23:25.771 --> 00:23:30.609 align:middle line:84%
will the heart fibrillate
without an artery blockage?

00:23:30.609 --> 00:23:31.577 align:middle line:90%
>> Christian Wilde: Yes.

00:23:31.577 --> 00:23:33.779 align:middle line:84%
If you have and that's
unfortunate.

00:23:33.779 --> 00:23:35.247 align:middle line:90%
They are not very effective

00:23:35.247 --> 00:23:39.017 align:middle line:84%
in treating atrial
fibrillation, AFib.

00:23:39.017 --> 00:23:42.488 align:middle line:84%
Many of you probably have
family members that have it.

00:23:42.488 --> 00:23:44.923 align:middle line:90%
And it's here's what happens.

00:23:44.923 --> 00:23:48.994 align:middle line:84%
If the heart fibrillates
just a little bit,

00:23:48.994 --> 00:23:53.332 align:middle line:84%
the blood thats being
sent by the atrium

00:23:53.332 --> 00:23:59.071 align:middle line:84%
to the ventricle clots in
that couple of seconds.

00:23:59.071 --> 00:24:04.910 align:middle line:84%
So, the importance is that you
must never miss your medication.

00:24:04.910 --> 00:24:09.381 align:middle line:84%
I know somebody who did and
she's in a retirement home now.

00:24:09.381 --> 00:24:10.616 align:middle line:90%
>> George Noory: Blood thinners?

00:24:10.616 --> 00:24:11.617 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
Blood thinners, yes.

00:24:11.617 --> 00:24:12.818 align:middle line:90%
You have to take it.

00:24:12.818 --> 00:24:15.454 align:middle line:84%
You have to be religious
about it.

00:24:15.454 --> 00:24:18.624 align:middle line:84%
They came up with a drug called
Pradaxa, everybody was excited.

00:24:18.624 --> 00:24:21.894 align:middle line:90%
Then 2500 people died from it.

00:24:21.894 --> 00:24:26.231 align:middle line:84%
Coumadin apparently is still
the drug of choice for it.

00:24:26.231 --> 00:24:28.133 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: Let's talk
about some natural remedies.

00:24:28.133 --> 00:24:31.036 align:middle line:84%
Things that people can
do at home right now

00:24:31.036 --> 00:24:33.939 align:middle line:84%
to make their heart
tick a little longer.

00:24:33.939 --> 00:24:35.941 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde:
A little longer.

00:24:35.941 --> 00:24:40.279 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that
helps control fibrillation

00:24:40.279 --> 00:24:44.116 align:middle line:84%
and the electrical part of your
heart is your magnesium level.

00:24:44.116 --> 00:24:46.618 align:middle line:84%
And I wonder how many
of us I check myself.

00:24:46.618 --> 00:24:47.953 align:middle line:90%
I went down there.

00:24:47.953 --> 00:24:52.558 align:middle line:84%
I said to the doctor, "I want
you to do a vitamin D test

00:24:52.558 --> 00:24:54.593 align:middle line:90%
and a magnesium test."

00:24:54.593 --> 00:24:57.596 align:middle line:84%
I was below the scale
on magnesium.

00:24:57.596 --> 00:25:01.867 align:middle line:84%
Magnesium can help
women lower their risk

00:25:01.867 --> 00:25:04.736 align:middle line:90%
of sudden death by 77 percent.

00:25:04.736 --> 00:25:07.472 align:middle line:84%
And these are things
like George just said.

00:25:07.472 --> 00:25:10.842 align:middle line:84%
What are some of the natural
things why are we living longer?

00:25:10.842 --> 00:25:11.910 align:middle line:90%
Because of knowledge.

00:25:11.910 --> 00:25:14.046 align:middle line:84%
We know because we
just talked about it.

00:25:14.046 --> 00:25:15.847 align:middle line:90%
You got to check your magnesium.

