It's heavily in involved
homocysteine levels.

00:25:54.419 --> 00:25:57.823 align:middle line:84%
Homocysteine is involved
now as a risk factor.

00:25:57.823 --> 00:25:59.091 align:middle line:84%
>> George Noory: And
explain what that is.

00:25:59.091 --> 00:26:03.061 align:middle line:84%
>> Christian Wilde: Homocysteine
is a sulfur containing

00:26:03.061 --> 00:26:04.796 align:middle line:90%
amino acid.

00:26:04.796 --> 00:26:08.200 align:middle line:84%
And they've kind of played it
down for the past few years.

00:26:08.200 --> 00:26:10.802 align:middle line:84%
Though there was a lot
of attention to it.

00:26:10.802 --> 00:26:14.373 align:middle line:84%
If your homocysteine
levels is elevated,

00:26:14.373 --> 00:26:17.709 align:middle line:84%
and you're taking niacine,
it will raise 50 percent.

00:26:17.709 --> 00:26:20.812 align:middle line:84%
